There is no cobblestone generator in this pack. You must gather pebbles and then convert other items into EMC to create more cobblestone.

Shift right click dirt to recieve pebbles.

Transmutation is staged so you must progress through the pack and level up your skills before you are able to create things such as diamonds from EMC. Be careful if you consume an item that you do not have the requirements for you will not be able to get it back out.

This quest will teach you some about the basics of Reskillable; the mod that is used for staging a large variety of things in this pack.

To get to the skill menu for Reskillable, press 'y' or click on the tab to the left of your inventory.

To start with I recommend using the level you got for completing the Tinker's Quest to level up technology. This will allow you to start using crafting tables so that you can further progress.

Open up the skills menu and select "Tech", and then hit the '+' sign at the top right to put your level into it.
If you are tired of taking a beating from the mobs you fight. Craft an Armor Station and build yourself a set of armor.
Make a Blood Altar to start delving into Blood Magic.
Create a Weak Blood Orb and right click with it to create your soul network.

Each drop has its own requirements and mobs that it can drop from once those requirements are met. After meeting the requirements on the right you can get Gold Ore from killing:

Endermen
Villagers
Zombie Pigmen
Zombie Villagers
Craft and fire up a clay bucket.

Each drop has its own requirements and mobs that it can drop from once those requirements are met. After meeting the requirements on the right you can get Coal from killing:

Bats
Creepers
Ghasts
Spiders
Squids
Wither Skeletons
Zombies
Hold a clay bucket in your hand while it is raining to collect water.
Chop the wood.

Craft the table to make tinker tools. If you are not already Tech 2 from killing mobs I recommend you use the level to get it.

When you get to the point that you decide to make armor, start by making an Armor Station.

Build a mob farm!

Not only are mob farms good for experience to level up, as you level up killing mobs will give you different resources. (Note: Looting increases the chance of mobs dropping resources.)

I recommend making some sort of mob dropper that pushes them into a hole using water. This way you can quickly kill the mobs as they will be low on health.
Just a small prick of your finger.
Slates are used for crafting runes and a lot of other things in Blood Magic.

Throw redstone, nether quartz, and charged certus quartz into a puddle to create fluix crystals.
Create a Ritual Diviner, and use it to set up a Well of Suffering below one of your blood altars. This will allow you to start collecting blood which you will need for some of the EMC Seed tiers.

Just a muffler for obnoxious sounds.
Make a simple circuit and then craft yourself a generator.

Your blood altar can be upgraded by placing runes around the edge. Use the Inspectoris Scandalum to see what is needed for the next tier.

Note: Blank Runes can be replaced with different runes to provide your blood altar with different effects.

Proceed to get some craft a Industrial Blast furnace. Once created you will need to build the multiblock structure using standard maching casing. It is a 3x3x4 structure with 2 spaces in the middle. You will need this in order to get steel which opens up other mods.

Later on you will need to put lava in those two empty spots as it will increase the max temperature.
A wrench is required for picking up the tech reborn machines. Without it you will lose the majority of the machine.
Enhanced Energy Conduits allow you to transfer eight times as much energy as normal Energy Conduits.
Speed runes increase the speed at which the Blood Altar can infuse items.
Better machine casing means your blast furnace can reach higher heat levels.
Will increase the amount of Life Essence gathered from sacrificing mobs.
Will increase the amount of Life Essence gathered from using the sacrificial dagger.
You will end up needing to make a rolling machine to make some of the more advanced tech reborn machines later on.
Even better machine casing means your blast furnace can reach even higher heat levels.
Increases the max capacity of your blood altar.

When paired with Runes of Sacrifice, a mob spawner, and a Well of Suffering, Displacement Runes allow for pumping out of a Blood Altar at an increased rate. This allows for having a dedicated blood collection altar.

Note: Displacement Runes are also limited by the internal tank's capacity so you should also add in a few Runes of Capacity.

Using your livingrock pedestal and hammer smash various items into the base Thaumcraft Crystals:

Aer : Sky Stone
Terra : Grass
Ignis : Magma Block
Aqua : Waterstone
Ordo : Packed Ice
Perditio : Obsidian

Combine three different crystal types with redstone dust, flint, and a bowl to create salis mundo.

Start by dropping a vis crystal onto the ground and then picking it up. Sleeping will give you "Strange Dreams", which will allow you to create a thaumonomicon.

Right click a bookshelf with a piece of salis mundo to create a thaumonomicon.
You can use Flux points and plugs to wirelessly tranfer energy. Plugs accept energy and points output energy.
You can control your network via a Flux Controller. You can also wirelessly charge your inventory via the settings in the Flux Controller.
You can use a Flux Configurator to copy network settings from one flux plug/point to another.
Get to max level in all skills.
To quickly travel between two set points you can create Travel Anchors. Looking at another travel anchor and jumping/crouching while on one will teleport you to it.

Using a Staff of Travelling will let you teleport to travel anchors from a longer distance (while also not requiring you to be standing on one). You can also sneak right click with a staff of travelling to teleport a brief distance in the direction you are looking.
Enhanced Ender IO Machines are even faster and more efficient than the normal versions.

To improve your farm, and allow for mobs to spawn when there are no players nearby created a Powered Spawner. Powered Spawners can spawn mobs more frequently and their speed can be changed based on the capacitor used.
Create mystical fertilizer, and use it on grass to begin recieving botania flowers.
Craft some pure dasies to kick start botania.
Craft a mana pool and mana spreader to begin storing mana

Endoflames are great passive mana generation if you can automate dropping fuel onto the flowers.

This works even better than with solidified fuel from Tinker I/O.
When you need a larger amount of portable mana, create a band of mana.
When you need an even larger amount of portable mana, create a greater band of mana.
Create a Runic Altar to start making runes.
Collect some aquamarine to begin your journey to greater understanding.

JEI will be able to help you get from the essence to the EMCable outcome, as well as, help you upgrade from one tier of seed to the next.

If you want to get into Astral Sorcery you will have to start by making an Orechid to get aquamarine ore.

Now that you have collected some aquamarine you can start getting into Astral Sorcery and create your first Luminous Crafting Table, and Resonating wand.

Start by placing down the crystal with direct line of sight of the sky and place a vanilla crafting table nearby. Next right click the crystal with the linking tool and then right click the crafting table. This will link the crystal to the table.

Note: The crystal you were given is not of the best quality, and you will be able to make better crystals as you progress through Astral Sorcery.
Use your linking tool to aim the crystal at a block of aquamarine. Overtime this will turn into rock crystal ore which you can break to get rock crystals.
To start making liquid starlight which has many uses your first task will be to create a lightwell. You can put aquamarine and rock crystals in it at night to convert into liquid starlight.
Create a Starlight Crafting Altar to learn more about Attunement.
Create a looking glass and start looking at the stars.
Upgrade your handheld looking glass to a full fledged telescope.
Using the linking tool link the crystal to iron ore and create star metal ore.
Craft some constelation papers and hold onto them to discover some information about the stars. You can sneak right click with your astral tome to store the written papers inside.
The next step in your journey is to attune yourself to a constelation that you have discovered. Create an attunement altar and when it lights up with the constelation you want jump in.
An altar to teach you the ways of the constellations.
Create a Starlight Infuser to start being able to infuse items with starlight.

Combine a rock crystal and star metal dust inside a pool of liquid starlight.

With a visible sky it will combine and grow into celestial crystals.
Create an Iridecent Altar to learn more about Radiance.
Create an observatory to be able to view faint constellations.

Create a Containment Chalice to allow for better storage of liquid starlight. When starlight infusion would normally drain starlight from the multiblock, it can instead draw the starlight from a nearby chalice. This saves you the need of having to replace the liquid starlight.
Create a Nether Cake and hand it in to get the obsidian required to make a nether portal.
Gather the resources for a Tinker's Construct Smeltery. This will allow you to use metal to make better tools and armor.

Tinker I/O allows for speeding up the melting process with a fuel input machine, and for faster solidifying using a smart output.

One of the best fuels in the game is added by Tinker I/O, and is called Solidified Fuel. It lasts 25 times longer than coal and is a lot cheaper EMC wise.
Create a creative energy cube, and never have to worry about power again.
Ever find yourself looking for more of a specific fluid? Well look now more for a limited time only get your infinite fluid needs here.
Complete your quest for being the best floral alchemist by creating a pool that gives infinite mana.
If you want more bang for your buck you can make Enhancement Crystals to upgrade your infinity gear even further.
Turn that infinite fluid into infinite gas.
When you decide you want to store all your items in a single ME cell, create a Creative ME Storage Cell.
Tired of taking a beating from mobs, and your troll friends? Create a set of Infinity Armor.
When you decide you want to be able to kill anything and anyone in one hit build a Sword of the Cosmos.
The first item you encounter that is more expensive than the maximum value of EMC you can hold.

Craft a Tome of Knowledge to learn how to create all items that have an EMC value.

Note: You must put the Tome in the "Burn Slot" in the transmutation table, putting it on the left will not teach you the knowledge.
Create a copper chest to increase your available storage per chest.
Create an iron chest to increase your available storage per chest.
Create a diamond chest to increase your available storage per chest.
Create a silver chest to increase your available storage per chest.
Create a gold chest to increase your available storage per chest.
When you need to store a lot of a single type of material, either make some storage drawers, or use Mekanism bins.
Double a drawer's storage space.
Quadruple a drawer's storage space.
8x a drawer's storage space.
16x a drawer's storage space.
32x a drawer's storage space.
Travel to the nether and kill blazes. Collect their rods and convert them to blaze powder. Throwing blaze powder into water will produce lava, so be careful.
Item Storage
Build an ME System to store all your items and no longer have a need for chests.
Fluid Storage
Essentia Storage
Gas Storage
To gather loot and xp from your mob farm, create a Vacuum chest and an XP Vacuum.
To store experience and not worry about it if you die, create an experience obelisk. This also lets you share xp with other players if you are on a server.
When you want to start autocrafting using your ME system, create a Molecular Assembler, and some interfaces. You will also need Crafting Storage.
The first capacitor you will make, required to run your new machines.
Upgraded version of Basic Capacitors.
Upgraded version of Double-Layered Capacitors.
Upgraded version of Octadict Capacitors.
Upgraded version of Crystalline Capacitors.
Upgraded version of Melodic Capacitors. Stellar Capacitors are the best capacitors in this pack.
Crystalline Energy Conduits allow you to transfer twice as much energy as Ender Energy Conduits.
Crystalline Pink Slime Energy Conduits allow you to transfer twice as much energy as Crystalline Energy Conduits.
Melodic Energy Conduits allow you to transfer four times as much energy as Crystalline Pink Slime Energy Conduits.
Stellar Energy Conduits are the best energy conduits or cables for that matter that you can make.
Ender Energy Conduits allow you to transfer four times as much energy as Enhanced Energy Conduits.

This is likely one of the first energy conduits/cables you will make. There are some slightly cheaper ones from Ender IO Endergy that don't transfer as much power, as well as the insulated copper cables from Tech Reborn you can use before you start making better power transfer.
For item transfer the first transfer method you will probably make is item conduits from Ender IO.

To transfer gas you have a couple options. You can use Mekanism's Pressurized Tubes, or you can use Gas Conduits. Gas Conduits are Ender IO styled conduits for gas so they work in the conduit bundles and you can make your structures more condensed.

With Ender Gas Conduits you can also use Gas Filters so that you can have gas travelling through the same pipe so long as it knows where it is going to be outputted.
For fluid transfer you can use mechanical pipes from Mekanism, or use Ender IO's fluid conduits.
The most basic Ender IO machines, they are not that efficient, and run very slowly but they will get the job done.
Create an inscriber and start making circuits to make your own computer storage system.
You can upgrade your simple Ender IO machines to their normal variants. These variants require capacitors, but the better the capacitor the faster the machine is and the more energy it can store.
Creating a farming station will be very useful for purposes of automating farming EMC.
Create a slice'n'splice to start making Z-Logic Controllers, which you will need for some of the higher end Ender IO Machines.
You will need to make a Soul Binder to get Ender Crystals, used in creating a Staff of Travelling.
To transfer items, fluids, gas over a distance you can use Quantum Entangloporters. (Think tesseracts)
An empowerer is used to empower various items to a more powerful state.
An atomic reconstructor lets you convert items of one type into items of another type.

There are multiple uses for an Advanced Reconstructor. Firstly it has an inventory so you don't need to drop items on the ground, because you can use its internal buffer. And secondly it has a higher energy limit than a normal Atomic Reconstructor. This is needed for some of the later tiers of EMC seeds.

To start upgrading your Mekanism machines you can either craft them into basic factories, or you can use a basic tier installer.

One thing to note about the installers, is you still are required to meet the requirements of the next tier machine to be able to upgrade to that tier factory.

To continue upgrading your Mekanism machines you can either craft them into advanced factories, or you can use an advanced tier installer.

One thing to note about the installers, is you still are required to meet the requirements of the next tier machine to be able to upgrade to that tier factory.

To finish upgrading your Mekanism machines you can either craft them into elite factories, or you can use an elite tier installer.

One thing to note about the installers, is you still are required to meet the requirements of the next tier machine to be able to upgrade to that tier factory.
A Metallurgic Infuser allows you to infuse simple items with various other materials.
The Enrichment chamber lets you improve the effictiveness of various items in the metallurgic infuser, as well as, allow you to double lots of resources that come from ores.
Compress items in the Enrichment Chamber to make them eight times more efficient in the Metallurgic Infuser.
This is the most basic Mekanism Alloy that is needed in a large number of Mekanism machines.
A more advanced alloy for Mekanism machines.
An even more advanced alloy for Mekanism machines.
The Industrial Machine Chassis is the second chassis you will probably end up creating. It is needed to make the majority of more advanced machines, and machine casings.
Steel Casings are the third tier of machine casings you will probably end up creating. They are used for all Mekanism machines and for creating even more advanced casings.

The simplest machine chassis you can make. To get the Grains of Infinite light the bedrock in the center of your starting platform on fire and wait for it to burn out. There is a 50% chance that grains of infinity will drop.
Use a livingrock pedestal to crush various materials into new things.
Right clicking curiosities gives random research and knowledge for Thaumcraft. Once you reach 100 warp killing any mob that drops amber also has a chance of dropping preserved curiosities.
To use Ore Excavation you must meet the requirements listed on the right.
Create a cloud stepper's ring to gain the ability to double jump.
One of the earliest versions of flight you can get is a Mekanism Jetpack.
Build a thaumometer and start scanning all the things.
Crafting with Essentia.
Create a research table and start researching more thaumcraft.
Create a crucible to be able to create even more things.
Smelt items in an essentia smeltery to extract the essentia from them.
Build a sanity checker and see how insane you are becoming.
A workbench charger allows you to charge your Arcane Workbench, and extend the range of it to 3x3 chunks instead of just the chunk it is in.
Wands can be used as reusable salis mundo.
Unlock Auromancy in your Thaumonomicon.
Unlock Alchemy in your Thaumonomicon.
Unlock Artifice in your Thaumonomicon.
Unlock Infusion in your Thaumonomicon.
Unlock Golemancy in your Thaumonomicon.
Unlock Eldritch in your Thaumonomicon.
A Caster's Gauntlet is used to start the infusion process. Right click the Runic Matrix with the gauntlet to begin the infusion process.
Goggles of revealing will allow you to see the different aspects that make up various things.
Upgrading your chassis to a soul chassis, will allow you to create some machines that are useful for mob and xp farming.
Use mana lenses to change the effects of mana bursts, from mana spreaders.
You can use a mana charger to automate charging items that need mana.
Create a Mana Tablet to power various handheld items.
You can use sparks to transfer mana.
When you need even more mana storage, create a mana buffer. Mana buffers accept mana from the neighbouring pools and output to a pool placed ontop of itself.
Create some terrasteel.
Livingrock Barrels can fill neighboring Petal Apothocaries with water assuming the barrel has water to supply it with.

One of the more interesting generating flowers there are. The Dandelifeon produces mana by simulating Conway's Game of Life. This is one of the highest generating mana flowers there is, and can be fully automated.
Throw some manasteel into an elven portal to get elementium.
Create some manasteel.
Build a lightning rod and put iron fences on top of it. The more fences you have the higher chance lightning will strike during a thunderstorm.
To make your ME crafting go faster add some Crafting Co-Processors to your Crafting Storage.

To finish upgrading your Mekanism storage containers, you can either craft them into the ultimate versions, or you can use an ultimate tier installer.

One thing to note about the installers, is you still are required to meet the requirements of the next tier machine to be able to upgrade to that tier factory.

Attach a Lens of the Killer to an atomic reconstructor and activate it to damage mobs. Killed mobs drop XP and player only drops.

NOTE: These mobs will not drop any of the ores from Murdering for Ores.

Tech Reborn's Fusion reactor allows for a decent source of early midgame power generation. If you want you can use it for later game power generation as well, you just need to create a larger sized reactor.
Solar panels are a good form of renewable energy. They don't have an EMC value though so if you want the higher tier panels you should make sure to set up some automation.

A Philosopher's Stone is very useful, you can use it to turn mobs from one kind to another, transform various blocks. (This lets you get rubber, silverwood, and greatwood saplings if you somehow lose yours.)

As you progress you will end up using the mob transmutation feature to create evokers to get blue hearts, and Vindicators for more reliable emerald drops. Once your taming level is high enough you can also use this to transform passive mobs into pets and tame them.
Gather the parts for a Mekanism fusion reactor. When supplied the proper fuel this is one of the best energy options for mid game.
Using a Swiftwolf's Rending Gale you can have creative flight, as long as oyu have EMC in your inventory to fuel it.
Instead of having to carry around a transmutation table everywhere and remember to pick it back up after you are done using it; creating a Transmutation Tablet will make your life much easier.
Using a Ring of Arcana, you get a lot of benefits. The main one being the creative flight from the Swiftwolf's Rending Gale, except without the EMC cost for flight.
Create an Iron Alloy Furnace to make bronze.
Create a Drawer Controller so that you can just pump all your mob drops into it and have them be transfered to attached drawers.

Lots of high end resources come from killing villagers. This quest will explain some of the basics of curing villagers, and then breeding them. I also recommend getting looting 3 as that will ensure villagers drop some sort of resource.

To get a villager, start by isolating a Zombie Villager and applying a splash potion of weakness to it. Then feed it a regular golden apple. Within 2-5 minutes it will turn into a villager. (I recommend encasing it during this time as you will need at least two villagers to start breeding them.)
Note: Using the philosopher's stone to turn passive mobs into villagers is disabled.

This is a rough overview of how villager breeding works. Villagers will only breed if they are "willing". Feed your villagers, bread, carrots, or potatoes. I recommend bread as it has the lowest EMC value and only requires 3 pieces per villager rather than 12. To breed they also require the population to be less than ~35% of the "village". The size of the "village" is based on how many doors there are making up a village. A valid door must be within the village radius where the number of blocks within 5 spaces "outside" is not the same as on the other side ("inside").

(The minecraft wiki has a decent page on the subject of breeding called "Villager Farming". So I recommend reading that for a more detailed explanation and some example videos.)

While the Farmer may not be quite as efficient as a Farming Station, it will get the job done for producing EMC early via EMC seeds.

Note: The range for the farmer is 5x5 as apposed to the usual 9x9.
